      <abstract>
        <p>Roundup of advertising account changes (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Coca-Cola North America, Atlanta, to Siboney USA, New York, part of True North Communications, to handle the first Coca-Cola Classic brand promotions account aimed at Spanish-speaking customers. Billings have not been determined.  Royal Olympic Cruises, Athens, to Black Ink Marketing, New York, to handle its North American account, which had been at Korey Kay &amp; Partners, New York. Billings were estimated at $5 million.</p>
      </block>
